The new electoral laws require voters to present an identity document with a photograph, in addition to a test of American citizenship.
On the other hand, these laws reduce voting periods in advance, invalidate the right to register as an elector on the day of the election and withdraw the right to vote to citizens with criminal record.
Before the 2006 elections, no American state required voters to present an identity document with a photograph.
